com.tractrac.model.lib.api

Class ModelLocator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tractrac.model.lib.api.ModelLocator

  • public class ModelLocator
extends java.lang.Object

    This class is a locator used to get the instance of some of the factories that are used for the creation of the objects. Is the entry point of the library, and the unique class with statics methods.

    The principal object is the IEvent, that can be created using the IEventFactory singleton. This object represent the model of an event.

    The implementation of the singletons has to be registered using the Service Loader pattern. If you want to add a new implementation, you have to create a new component, create a file with the name of the interface in META-INF/services/ and add a line with the name of the implementation.

    Author:
    Jorge Piera Llodrá
    See Also:
    Locator, Service Loader
